body:
@pirapira any recent thoughts on this? I don't think we should do away with VMTests, but perhaps could limit their scope. It doesn't feel good to have KEVM have two versions of several opcodes, one just for VMTests.

Perhaps the VMTests that only deal with VM-related stuff could remain (eg. arithmetic, local memory ops, program counter ops), and anything that deals with Ethereum-specific state could be translated into GeneralStateTests instead?

I've become interested in this because I'm in the middle of refactoring the KEVM control-flow to make it more uniform to make doing proofs with KEVM easier (and also to support more uniform typed exceptions), but there are several spots where special cases are made for VMTests mode which are causing me headache.
